    The density of the Normal distribution is given by

    .. math::
        f(x) := \frac{1}{\sigma\sqrt{2\pi}} e^{ -\frac{(x-\mu)^2}{2\sigma^2} }

    Parameters
    ==========

    mu : Real number, the mean
    sigma : Real number, :math:`\sigma^2 > 0` the variance

